.RS
.LP
\fIAcc0\fR\& is returned if the table is empty\&. This function is similar to \fIlists:foldl/3\fR\&\&. The table elements are traversed in an unspecified order, except for \fIordered_set\fR\& tables, where they are traversed first to last\&.
.LP
If \fIFunction\fR\& inserts objects into the table, or another process inserts objects into the table, those objects \fIcan\fR\& (depending on key ordering) be included in the traversal\&.
.RE
