.nf

.B
foldr(Function, Acc0, Tab) -> Acc1
.br
.fi
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Function = fun((Element :: term(), AccIn) -> AccOut)
.br
Tab = tab()
.br
Acc0 = Acc1 = AccIn = AccOut = term()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
\fIAcc0\fR\& is returned if the table is empty\&. This function is similar to \fIlists:foldr/3\fR\&\&. The table elements are traversed in an unspecified order, except for \fIordered_set\fR\& tables, where they are traversed last to first\&.
.LP
If \fIFunction\fR\& inserts objects into the table, or another process inserts objects into the table, those objects \fIcan\fR\& (depending on key ordering) be included in the traversal\&.
.RE
